Acceptance findings resolved during this run
--------------------------------------------
- Updated migration expectations from 0008 to 0009 and removed a deterministic in-memory
  Artifact-key collision in repeated PostgreSQL fixtures.
- Fixed Candidate Answer Session projection aliasing: focus.version had overwritten
  session.version in the PostgreSQL result, causing legitimate Voice uploads to receive stale
  versions.
- Made public functional error mapping robust across duplicated Next.js server chunks while
  deriving HTTP status only from the closed internal error-code table.
- Closed accepted Invitations during empty Focus termination. This releases the partial unique
  Cohort Seat index and allows the next queued Interest to receive the recycled Attention Slot.
- Scoped Playwright locators to the full-screen dialog and exact error text; browser focus signals
  are explicitly dispatched in headless Chromium because tab visibility is not deterministic in
  headless mode.

